le", "sentiment": "neutral/engaged", "_matched_ai": true, "last_contact_date": "2025-05-13"}, {"name": "Navjot Singh", "risk": "Referenced as a planned meeting (SF Next_Step, 13 Mar 2026) but never appears as an attendee in any discovered Avoma call.", "role": "Influencer", "email": "navjotsingh@mtr.com.hk", "title": "Procurement Head - Centre of Excellence, Procurement Transformation", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role", "sentiment": "unknown", "_matched_ai": true}, {"name": "CHAN Chris Wing Keung", "risk": "Attended the 14 Jul 2025 solution-demo invitation, but the meeting was not recorded so content is unverified.", "role": "Unknown", "email": "chriswkchan@mtr.com.hk", "title": "Land Surveyor", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role", "sentiment": "unknown", "_matched_ai": true, "last_contact_date": "2025-07-14"}, {"name": "Brian Downie", "risk": "Named only via OpportunityContactRole; no call attendance or Next_Step mention found.", "role": "Unknown", "email": "bdownie@mtr.com.hk", "title": "Deputy Director - Procurement", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role", "sentiment": "unknown", "_matched_ai": true}, {"name": "Chauncy Chow, MBA", "role": "Evaluator", "email": "chowtshh@mtr.com.hk", "title": "Procurement Contract Manager", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role"}, {"name": "Pui Yi Pui Lee", "role": "Influencer", "email": "cathylee@mtr.com.hk", "title": "Procurement Manager", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role", "_role_inferred": true}, {"name": "Martino Stampanoni", "role": "Evaluator", "email": "martinostampanoni@mtr.com.hk", "title": "Procurement", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role", "_role_inferred": true}]}, "meddpicc": {"metrics": {"status": "gap", "sources": ["SF Next_Step 03 Mar 2025", "SF Next_Step 19 May 2025"], "narrative": "MTR articulated qualitative pain (migrating Oracle EBS procurement modules and wanting to start a GenAI use case, working with Arcblue on business process re-engineering; SF Next_Step, 3 Mar 2025) and asked Zycus for 'a first $ estimation' after the 13 May 2025 eAuction demo (SF Next_Step, 19 May 2025), but no quantified savings, cost reduction, or ROI figure has ever been delivered back or discussed in any subsequent log entry through the 9 Jun 2026 RFP issuance. Quantifying that estimate remains the single biggest open ask."}, "champion": {"status": "gap", "sources": ["SF Next_Step 08 Dec 2025", "Avoma calls 27 Feb / 10 Apr / 13 May 2025"], "narrative": "No champion or executive sponsor has been identified: the Next_Step log states explicitly 'Not able to identify champion/exec sponsor engagement' as of 8 Dec 2025, and no later entry reverses that. Simon Fung and Chauncy Chow are the recurring working-level contacts across the three content-bearing calls (27 Feb, 10 Apr, 13 May 2025) but neither has been confirmed as an internal advocate driving the tender internally or pushing back on EY's iCertis preference."}, "competition": {"status": "confirmed", "sources": ["SF Competitor field", "SF Next_Step 05 Nov 2025"], "narrative": "iCertis is the reconciled, current strongest threat: EY, MTR's tender advisory partner, has pushed for iCertis since at least 5 Nov 2025, and Zycus is 'working with Alliance to mitigate' with no evidence of success logged since. Sirion Labs is also listed on the Competitor field but has no corroborating mention in any call, Next_Step entry, or task, making it a materially lower and unconfirmed current threat by comparison."}, "identify_pain": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["SF Next_Step 03 Mar 2025", "Avoma E-Auction Demo call 13 May 2025"], "narrative": "MTR's stated pain spans two threads: an operational/CLM-adjacent pain around migrating Oracle EBS procurement modules while wanting to start a GenAI use case (SF Next_Step, 3 Mar 2025, working with partner Arcblue on 'BPR'), and a functional pain in the eAuction process where a buyer-side speaker said 'there is a need for transparency in the auction process, but buyers should not be required to monitor it as closely as the stock market' (Avoma E-Auction Demo, 13 May 2025). The pain owner for the CLM thread is the procurement/sourcing team; no single named pain owner has been confirmed beyond that."}, "paper_process": {"status": "gap", "sources": ["SF Next_Step 10 Apr 2025", "SF Next_Step 28 Apr 2025"], "narrative": "No contracting mechanics (MSA, legal review, procurement channel, InfoSec) have been discussed for the CLM opportunity in any source; the deal is still at RFP-scoring stage. The one paper-process precedent on record is an NDA signed for a related eAuction POC in Apr 2025, which does not extend to CLM contracting. Visibility here would come from tracking what MTR's procurement/legal team requires once the RFP scoring concludes."}, "economic_buyer": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["SF OpportunityContactRole (Alex Gautier)", "SF Next_Step 31 Oct 2025"], "narrative": "Alex Gautier, General Manager - Procurement & Supply Chain, is named as Decision Maker on the OpportunityContactRole (agautier@mtr.com.hk), but he does not appear as an attendee on any of the 4 Avoma-discovered calls spanning Feb 2025 to Jul 2025, nor in any later Next_Step entry naming a direct meeting with him. A 'Meeting with CPO next week' was logged 31 Oct 2025 but no outcome or attendee was ever confirmed in subsequent notes. Budget authority remains unreached."}, "decision_process": {"status": "confirmed", "sources": ["SF Next_Step 07 Jul 2025", "SF Next_Step 05 Nov 2025", "SF Next_Step 13 Mar 2026", "SF Next_Step 09 Jun 2026"], "narrative": "The process is traceable end to end in the Next_Step log: RFI (Jun 2025) -> use-case demos -> shortlisting confirmed 7 Jul 2025 -> a year-long clarification and exec-engagement cycle -> a project freeze (~4 May 2026) -> formal RFP issuance 9 Jun 2026 (PQ114354). EY, an external advisory partner, supports MTR's tender process and has been pushing for iCertis since 5 Nov 2025; MTR's Procurement Centre of Excellence head (Navjot Singh) was also due to be met around 13 Mar 2026. Vendor selection was previously targeted for March 2026 (12 Jan 2026 entry) but slipped to the RFP stage instead."}, "decision_criteria": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["SF Next_Step 09 Jun 2025", "SF Next_Step 21 Jul 2025", "SF Next_Step 13 Apr 2026"], "narrative": "MTR ran a formal RFI for CLM (received 9 Jun 2025, responded 12 Jun 2025) and has raised discrete clarification rounds covering AI/GenAI capability (21 Jul 2025, responded 1 Aug 2025), pricing (25 Jul 2025), implementation and maintenance (1 Sep 2025), configuration (3 Oct 2025), and is now pending a risk-management session with procurement (13 Apr 2026). These rounds outline the real evaluation criteria even though MTR has not shared a consolidated scoring rubric."}}}